Anh - Anh
vroom
informal
■ verb (of a vehicle or its engine) make a roaring sound when travelling or running at high speed.
■ noun the roaring sound of an engine or motor vehicle.
Origin
1960s: imitative.

sentences.en: The doctrine of reasonable expectations by Victor Vroom, Professor of Business Administration from Yale University (Ph. D. and science at the University of Michigan) introduced, that an individual will act in a certain way based on their expectations about a certain result.

sentences.en: The doctrine of reasonable expectations by Victor Vroom , Professor of Business Administration from Yale University (Ph.D. and science at the University of Michigan) introduced, that an individual will act in a certain way based on their expectations about a certain result.
